.TH MODLOCK 8 "May 2026" "modlock" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
modlock \- manage automatic kernel module loading
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B modlock
.IR OPTION
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B modlock
prevents the kernel from loading modules in response to userspace requests,
by writing
.B /bin/true
to
.IR /proc/sys/kernel/modprobe .
A systemd unit re-applies the lock at every boot.
The lock is reversible at runtime via
.BR \-\-unlock .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-setup
Run
.BR \-\-update ,
.BR \-\-install ,
and
.B \-\-lock
in sequence.
.TP
.B \-\-update
Write the currently-loaded module list to
.IR /etc/modules .
.TP
.B \-\-lock
Write
.B /bin/true
to
.IR /proc/sys/kernel/modprobe .
.TP
.B \-\-unlock
Restore
.I /proc/sys/kernel/modprobe
to the path of the real
.BR modprobe (8).
.TP
.B \-\-install
Install the script to
.I /usr/local/sbin/modlock
and enable
.IR modlock.service .
Only needs to be run once.
.TP
.B \-\-uninstall
Disable and remove
.IR modlock.service ,
then run
.BR \-\-unlock .
Does not remove
.IR /usr/local/sbin/modlock .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /proc/sys/kernel/modprobe
Kernel modprobe helper path; written by
.B \-\-lock
and
.BR \-\-unlock .
.TP
.I /etc/modules
Module snapshot written by
.BR \-\-update ;
processed by
.B systemd\-modules\-load.service
at boot.
.TP
.I /etc/systemd/system/modlock.service
Installed by
.BR \-\-install .
.TP
.I /usr/local/sbin/modlock
Default installation path.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B 0
on success,
.B 1
on error,
.B 2
on bad arguments.
.SH NOTES
.B modlock
does not block direct
.BR insmod (8)
calls.
For a stronger, irreversible lock use
.B kernel.modules_disabled=1
via
.BR sysctl (8).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR modprobe (8),
.BR lsmod (8),
.BR insmod (8),
.BR sysctl (8),
.BR systemd\-modules\-load.service (8)
